                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">17th-century script;  trained, careful hand. <note>
                           <p>Unknown</p>
                           
                        </note>
                        <note>
                           <p>- Omitted letters or words are inserted interlineally, in at least two hands, on many folios: fols. <locus target="#15vb #16rb #18rb #20va #21rb #22vb #25ra #32rb #33vb #34ra"/>
                              <locus from="46va"/>b, <locus target="#47ra"/>etc.</p>
                           <p>- Omitted words are written in the main hand in the margins, “tie-marks” indicating their places in the text: fols. <locus target="#2rb #47v #57r #63r #68v #69va #70vb"/>(rubricated), <locus target="#71ra"/>
                              <locus from="71va"/>b.</p>
                           <p>- Dittographic mistakes are underlined, on fols. <locus target="#47vb #54vb #58ra"/>; erased on fol. <locus target="#33rb"/>.     </p>
                        </note>
