                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="other" xml:id="d2">
                       
                        <p>Quire marks are written in the left upper corner of the first leaf of the quire (only those of quire I-III are are decorated with red and black dots).</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="mixed" xml:id="d3">
                        <p>Gold tooled narrow floral frame along the sides and spine. Spine divided in seven bands with the gilded monogram of King Christian VII (reg. <locus from="1766" to="1808"/>), the title “Manuscript Abyssinicum”, four Danish state emblems; each band separated by two gilded horizontal lines.</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <p>Fol. <locus target="#1ra"/>: በስመ፡እግዚአብሔር፡ጽኑዕ፨ዘመነ፡መንግሥቱ፡ዘኤይትዌዳዕ፡መልዕልተ፡ነፈሳት፡ደባትረ፡ማያት፡ዘያረግዕ።ወበከርሠ፡ ደመና፡ ማየ፡ ባሕር፡ ዘያመጽእ፨ …(fol. <locus target="#1vb"/>)… ንጽሕፍ፡ እንከ፡ ዜና፡ ኂሩቱ፡ ወስነ፡ ገድሉ፡ ወጽንዓ፡ ኃይሉ፡…</p>
                           
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
